Type\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"74761cf258a26a86885bcd069cade797ee25b8822b23ab7328d56ef025aff440","event_uuid":"87efe16e-cfab-487f-b786-f24e02b72c12","position":{"commit_sha":"83344a638dda3cf17e40de718345a80f1cf70ea2","position":"1784767544941342969-87efe16e-cfab-487f-b786-f24e02b72c12"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-217_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"b3ee85f1-444b-4969-9577-fe7b5a242d7d","comments":[],"created_at":1784766749820767001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Problem\ntests/unit/test_overlap_retrieve.py::test_perf asserts a fixed 50ms wall-clock budget on a SINGLE run of rebar.llm.overlap.retrieve() over 300 digests (line 63-66). On a contended CI runner the sample inflates far past budget and fails the Verified gate for unrelated changes. Observed: Gerrit run 29964385401 (ubuntu py3.11) failed 'retrieve took 289.5 ms (budget < 50 ms)' while py3.12/py3.13/macos passed in the SAME run.\n\n## Proven root cause (rebar-debug)\nSingle-sample wall-clock time is not robust to shared-runner CPU scheduling contention. The function itself is fast: measured 1.6ms median / 2.1ms max / 0-of-20-over-budget locally (~30x margin). The 289.5ms CI sample is ~180x the true cost = transient runner contention, not algorithmic cost. Introduced by 6558e2bfa (2026-07-09). Changeable artifact: the single-sample measurement + hardcoded threshold at test_overlap_retrieve.py:66.\n\n## Fix\nMeasure the MINIMUM elapsed across N=5 runs (best-of-N) and assert min < budget. The min reflects the uncontended compute cost (at least one of N samples hits a quiet slice), so transient contention no longer flakes the gate; a real algorithmic regression slows every run including the min, so the guardrail retains teeth. Keep the 50ms budget (huge margin on the ~1.6ms true cost).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] test_perf measures best-of-N (min over >=5 runs), asserts min < budget; no single-sample assertion remains.\n- [ ] Robustness: a simulated transient stall on one sample no longer fails the assertion (whereas the old single-sample form does).\n- [ ] Teeth retained: a sustained/uniform slowdown (real regression) still fails the assertion.\n- [ ] make lint && make typecheck && make test green.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"tests/unit/test_overlap_retrieve.py","reason":"Change test_perf from single-sample wall-clock to best-of-N minimum to eliminate CI-contention flake while retaining regression teeth"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"c7aa69f3-bc34-42ed-9283-cfd36e68a5b8","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"5e94-3841-ebf0-4edd","ticket_type":"bug","title":"Flaky perf gate: test_overlap_retrieve.test_perf single-sample wall-clock budget breaks under CI runner contention","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["f536cf65-7be2-4b74-99d1-9b0d0de65710","ebce7522-96cd-4932-a26a-ca31a8767bdc","8cd64ee3-2fd0-4d43-8647-4c8d18c66986","c7aa69f3-bc34-42ed-9283-cfd36e68a5b8","e51a2fe5-693b-42e2-ae79-a67f3d447f27","87efe16e-cfab-487f-b786-f24e02b72c12"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784767544941342970,"uuid":"2f0e4b51-c21c-4912-9a76-dbfccd4e39ea"}